@khurshid-alam what is happening is that `-u` is telling rclone to always transfer the file as it is newer.  However dropbox has a bug which means when you update a file and **only** change the client_modified, it doesn't actually change the client modified :-(  Dropbox assumes the file is the same I think.

Normally rclone works around this by deleting the file first when it wants to update the modification time.

So either do the sync without `-u --no-update-modtime` or delete the offending file first.

@khurshid-alam 

`-u` is most useful for remotes which don't store modtimes.

Your proposed `-c --no-update-modtime` looks OK I think.
